[1] China - WHO update 4
Date: Mon 13 Feb 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News,
Mon 13 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_02_13a/en/index.html>

China: Avian Influenza situation - WHO Update 4
-----------------------------------------------
The Ministry of Health in China has reported the country's 12th
laboratory-confirmed case of human infection with H5N1 avian influenza virus.
The case occurred in a 20-year-old female farmer from the
south-central province of Hunan. She developed symptoms on 27 Jan
2006 and was subsequently hospitalized with severe pneumonia. Symptom
onset followed the culling of poultry raised by her household. She
died on 4 Feb 2006.
As of 13 Feb 2006, China has reported 12 laboratory-confirmed cases.
Of these, 8 have been fatal.
--
