[2] Indonesia - WHO update 3; and additional confirmed case
Date: Mon 13 Feb 2006
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News,
Mon 13 Feb 2006 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2006_02_13/en/index.html>

Indonesia: Avian Influenza Situation - WHO Update 3
-----------------------------------------------
As of Mon 13 Feb 2006, the Ministry of Health in Indonesia has
confirmed an additional 2 cases of human infection with H5N1 avian
influenza virus. Both cases were fatal.
The 1st case occurred in a 22-year-old woman who developed symptoms
on 25 Jan 2006 and died on 10 Feb 2006. Her neighbors kept chickens.
Samples from these chickens and from pet birds in a market near the
woman's home are being tested by Indonesia's animal health authorities.
The 2nd case occurred in a 27-year-old woman who developed symptoms
on 31 Jan 2006 and died on 10 Feb 2006. Deaths of chickens in her
neighborhood were reported 4 days prior to symptom onset.
The 2 women resided in different sub-districts of West Java Province.
The newly confirmed cases bring the total in Indonesia to 25. Of
these, 18 were fatal.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This is the official notification of confirmation from WHO, which
was reported by local sources yesterday (12 Feb 2006). Confirmation
of another suspected human case of avian influenza is still pending.
A male patient who contracted infection in November 2005 and
recovered has now been confirmed positive according to local sources
(see below). This brings the total of laboratory-confirmed cases of
human avian influenza in Indonesia to 26, with the total of
fatalities remaining 18. - Mod.CP]
